<h1>This project doesn't have any issues yet</h1>
<p>Here are some ways to add new issues:</p>

<div class="row-fluid add-issues">
  <div class="span3">
    <h3>1. Add from scratch</h3>
    <p>
      Just click on the <i class="fa fa-plus"></i> sign next to the
      <strong>Issues</strong> heading in the sidebar.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="offset1 span3">
    <h3>2. Import from a library</h3>
    <p>You'll need an import plugin like:</p>
    <ul class="fa-ul">
      <li><i class="fa fa-li fa-chevron-right"></i><a href="https://dradisframework.com/ce/addons/mediawiki.html?utm_source=ce&utm_medium=app" target="_blank">MediaWiki</a></li>
      <li><i class="fa fa-li fa-chevron-right"></i><a href="http://vulndbhq.com" target="_blank">VulnDB</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>And then:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Activate via <code>Gemfile.plugins</code></li>
      <li>
        Click on the 
        <%= link_to main_app.configurations_path do %><i class="fa fa-cog fa-lg"></i> Configuration<% end %> link at the top-right of the page.
      </li>
      <li>
        And on the <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i> next to <strong>Import
        issues</strong> in the sidebar.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <p>Or for an integrated option, check out the <a href="https://dradisframework.com/pro/add-ons/issuelib.html?utm_source=ce&utm_medium=app" target="_blank">IssueLibrary add-on</a></p>
  </div>

  <div class="offset1 span3">
    <h3>3. Upload tool output</h3>
    <p>Use the <%= link_to main_app.upload_manager_path do %><i class="fa fa-cloud-upload fa-lg"></i> Upload output from tool<% end %> link at the top of the page.</p>
  </div>
</div>
